            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I"
            },
            {
              "chord": "C7",
              "text": "still would"
            },
            {
              "chord": "F",
              "text": "struggle,"
            },
            {
              "chord": "Dm",
              "text": "scheme"
            },
            {
              "chord": "G7",
              "text": "and"
            },
            {
              "chord": "C",
              "text": "plot."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "1"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "It seems one comes to rob my home;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Afraid, yet stubborn, I persist,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I fear my final day has come—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "With every ounce of strength, resist."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He comes to wrestle; I defend:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I’ll fight Him to the bitter end."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "How strange! Though every wile I’ve used,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For one whole night, yet still He stands."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I see my strength has been reduced,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And yet revenge is not His plan."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "How strange! Although I can’t get free,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My courage grows exceedingly."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I’ve never met with such a foe,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And even if He states His name,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Of this opponent naught I know,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But that from Him reward I’d gain."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I’d force Him blessing to bestow,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And, blessing, His surrender own."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "’Tis dawn, yet have I won, or He?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "It’s still impossible to see."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My Rival, forced, now blesses me,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To me concedes the victory ."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Says “Israel” is my new name;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But when I rise, my thigh is lame."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The faintest light in darkened heart"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Begins to shine — I realize:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "If I’m so strong, why grasp the heel?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "If victor, why the crippled thigh?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "’Twas He who won and left this sign,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "From folly warning me thereby."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A flood of light: This heart of mine,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As breaks the dike by swelling tide,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "At once in radiance divine"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Must worship, and in shame must hide."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "So great my sin, I must confess:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I’m lawless, full of filthiness."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "7"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Alas! To think: I overcame"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Creator God Omnipotent!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Ridiculous! Oh, woe is me!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Death is my fitting punishment."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That these, mine own two hands, rebelled"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The mighty God to stop and held!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "8"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thou, God, dost shine so gloriously;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thou, Lord of hosts, resplendent, bright,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "At once, at recognizing Thee,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And realizing who Thou art,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I cry aloud, and tearfully"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I must repent and bow the knee."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "9"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "How can it be that I could see"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Him face to face and hand to hand?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "If only earth would swallow me,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My shame to hide, my life to end."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Why did I not, at life’s first start,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Pass on, from earth in sleep depart?"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "10"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I hate myself; my heart was dim,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For blinded were mine eyes by pride;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Now, at the thought of conquering Him,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I tremble and am terrified."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Not just my thigh, but all my strength"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I’ve lost; I’m broken, paralyzed."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "11"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As I look back at all my life,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I see that it’s corrupt entire."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For self, my God I sacrificed;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My foolish heart knew but desire."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What then I thought that “blessing” be"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Was forcing God to grant my plea."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "12"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“I wish: the heav’n must fall in line."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I plan: my Lord must coincide."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I want: my God should step aside."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I work: my God must be my guide."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When I am rushed, He must not stay,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For once, His victory to display.”"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "13"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "There’s one so evil here below,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "So proud, deceitful, obstinate;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Lord, that I’m Jacob Thou dost know:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "One Thou should’st but detest and hate;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "No hope have I but mercy Thine"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Upon this wretched heart of mine."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "14"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I grope — at once His mercy find."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "At first lame step — His grace is mine!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "If I forget, my wounded thigh"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Reminds: on naught can I rely."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Though Israel I’m named by Thee,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yet Jacob ever lame shall be."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "15"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "O Lord, ‘twas Thou that overcame;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In Thy defeat, defeat I’d claim;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To Thee I yield my victory;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thy weakness drops me to my knees."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In fear and trembling all my days"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thy will I’d do, Thy name I’d praise."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "16"
    }
  ],
